5. invenit hos plegios. Only one pledge is namedÍ¾ probably the clerk expected a second name. The reader must be prepared for this sort ol thing.

manucapere aliquem, to take a person in hand, to undertake to produce him, to become his manucaptor.

6. atteehiars, to take and keep hold of. Aman may be attached by (per) his goods and chattels, as when they are taken as a security for his appearance, or by (per) another person who becomes surety sor him.

8. abjuravit regnum. For the law about sanctuary and abjuration ol the realm see Bracton (f. 135 b). Abjuration seems to have been very common.
